<dd>HTML+ (a superset of Version 2, and the precursor to Version 3)
as of 8 Nov 1993, by David Raggett.  Includes some interesting possibilities.
<dt><A HREF="http://www.w3.org/hypertext/WWW/Arena/tour/start.html"><code>http://www.w3.org/hypertext/WWW/Arena/tour/start.html</code></A>
<dd>An overview of the proposed features of Version 3, and identification
of those proposals likely to be deferred until Version 3.1.
Also identifies access to a test browser designed to display the new
Version 3.0 features as part of the review process.
<dt><A HREF="http://www.hpl.hp.co.uk/people/dsr/html/CoverPage.html"><code>http://www.hpl.hp.co.uk/people/dsr/html/CoverPage.html</code></A>
<dd>An early draft of the text for a proposed Version 3 as a
(now expired) Internet RFC
by David Raggett.  This link is identical to
<code>http://www.hpl.hp.co.uk/people/dsr/html3/CoverPage.html</code>
<dt><A HREF="http://ppewww.ph.gla.ac.uk/~flavell/iso8859/iso8859-1.html"><code>http://ppewww.ph.gla.ac.uk/~flavell/iso8859/iso8859-1.html</code></A>
<dd>An excellent analysis of the relationship of the ISO8859 Latin-1
character set with HTML entities, including representational tables,
identification of browser implementation inconsistencies and
differing/invalid presenatation.
<dt><A HREF="http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~tilt/cgh/"><code>http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~tilt/cgh/</code></A>
<dd>This is my personal favorite of the many documents describing
